---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<section id="about" class="bg-paper-soft py-24 md:py-32">
  <div class="max-w-[1440px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-16">
      <!-- Label rail -->
      <div class="md:col-span-2 hidden md:block">
        <p class="v-label text-copper">About Leigh-Ann</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Narrative -->
      <div class="md:col-span-7" data-reveal>
        <p class="small-caps text-copper mb-4">Chapter Eight</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-7xl text-ink leading-[0.9] mb-10">
          A rare <span class="italic font-display-italic">range</span>.
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-ink text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-[34em]">
          <p class="drop-cap">
            I grew up in Gasparillo, a market town in southern Trinidad named for the oil refinery it sits beside. My first job at 18 was at Petrotrin, the national oil company, in the Office of the VP of Oil and Refining. I moved to New York in 2006 at age 21 and have been working in executive offices ever since.
          </p>
          <p>
            Along the way I trained as a chef at the Institute of Culinary Education with highest honors and built <em class="u-link">A Table For Four</em>, a pop-up dinner series that ran in New York, London, Wisconsin, and Grenada and was covered by the <em>New York Times</em>, <em>Eater</em>, and the <em>Washington Post</em>. That part of my life taught me how to curate, host, and operate at volume. The two careers have always informed each other.
          </p>
          <p>
            My corporate path went from BearingPoint through PwC, Third Bridge, Immunovant, and Ascend Wellness Holdings. I was sole EA to five C-suite executives at pre-IPO Immunovant by March 2020. I built Ascend's quarterly board cadence from zero. I work with Claude and Perplexity daily. I hold my Certified Administrative Professional credential, and I'm Salesforce Certified Platform Administrator.
          </p>
          <p>
            My approach is simple. Anticipate, don't react. Take ownership, don't just execute. Build systems that survive transitions. Treat confidentiality as default, not a policy. I'd like to work with executives who value that, whether embedded on their team or partnered fractionally.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Signature -->
        <div class="mt-16 flex items-end gap-8">
          <div>
            <p class="font-display-italic text-5xl text-copper leading-none">Leigh-Ann</p>
            <p class="mt-3 small-caps text-ink-muted">New York, 2026</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Inline facts column -->
      <aside class="md:col-span-3 md:pl-6 md:border-l md:border-rule" data-reveal>
        <p class="small-caps text-copper mb-6">At a glance</p>
        <dl class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <dt class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink-muted mb-1">Based</dt>
            <dd class="text-ink text-base leading-snug">Union City, New Jersey &middot; NYC tri-state area</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink-muted mb-1">Open to</dt>
            <dd class="text-ink text-base leading-snug">Hybrid or in-office senior EA roles, NYC. Fully remote fractional engagements.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink-muted mb-1">Sectors</dt>
            <dd class="text-ink text-base leading-snug">Biotech, biopharma, finance, fintech, public-company operations</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink-muted mb-1">Board work</dt>
            <dd class="text-ink text-base leading-snug">Board Member, Kind Kitchen Group (food-justice nonprofit)</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink-muted mb-1">Languages</dt>
            <dd class="text-ink text-base leading-snug">English (native). Trinidadian Creole (native).</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
